{
  "uid": "v12-4-multiprop",
  "title": "Grafana 12.4 \u2014 Multi-property Variables",
  "description": "12.4 added the ability to map many identifiers onto one logical variable value. This dashboard maps `dev`+`development` \u2192 `dev` and `prod`+`production` \u2192 `prod` so one `env` variable drives queries whether the label value is written long-form or short-form.",
  "tags": [
    "grafana-12",
    "v12.4",
    "variables",
    "multi-property",
    "v12-demo"
  ],
  "schemaVersion": 40,
  "version": 1,
  "editable": true,
  "refresh": "30s",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-15m",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "timepicker": {},
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      {
        "name": "ds_prom",
        "type": "datasource",
        "query": "prometheus",
        "refresh": 1,
        "current": {
          "text": "Prometheus",
          "value": "prom"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "env",
        "label": "Environment",
        "type": "custom",
        "description": "Grafana 12.4 multi-property variable \u2014 one option can carry multiple query values.",
        "multi": true,
        "includeAll": true,
        "allValue": ".*",
        "options": [
          {
            "text": "dev",
            "value": "dev",
            "selected": true
          },
          {
            "text": "development",
            "value": "dev",
            "selected": true
          },
          {
            "text": "staging",
            "value": "stg"
          },
          {
            "text": "prod",
            "value": "prod",
            "selected": true
          },
          {
            "text": "production",
            "value": "prod",
            "selected": true
          }
        ],
        "current": {
          "text": [
            "dev",
            "development",
            "prod",
            "production"
          ],
          "value": [
            "dev",
            "dev",
            "prod",
            "prod"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 10000,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "tags": [
        "demo-guide"
      ],
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "html",
        "content": "<div style=\"padding:1.2rem;background:#1a2a3a;border-left:4px solid #5794f2;border-radius:6px;font-family:system-ui\"><div style=\"font-size:.75rem;letter-spacing:.18em;color:#8aa9d0;margin-bottom:.3rem\">DEMO GUIDE</div><div style=\"font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:600;color:#fff;margin-bottom:.6rem\">Grafana 12.4 \u2014 Multi-property Variables</div><div style=\"display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem\"><div><div style=\"font-weight:600;color:#5794f2;margin-bottom:.2rem\">\ud83c\udfaf What you're looking at</div><div style=\"font-size:.88rem;color:#dfe7f0\">v12.4 multi-property variables map many display values to the same query value. Solves dev/development, prod/production once and for all.</div></div><div><div style=\"font-weight:600;color:#73bf69;margin-bottom:.2rem\">\ud83e\uddea Try this</div><div style=\"font-size:.88rem;color:#dfe7f0\">Pick both 'dev' and 'development' \u2014 they collapse to the same query value 'dev'. Same for prod/production.</div></div></div><div style=\"margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.6rem;border-top:1px solid #2d3e54;font-size:.85rem\">\ud83d\udcda <strong style=\"color:#fff\">Learn more</strong>: <a href=\"https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/dashboards/variables/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#ff9830\">Grafana docs</a> \u00b7 <a href=\"https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/whatsnew/whats-new-in-v12-4/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color:#ff9830\">v12 What's New</a></div></div>"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 7
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### Multi-property variables (12.4)\n\nThe `env` variable has five display options:\n\n| Display | Value sent to query |\n|---|---|\n| `dev`          | `dev`  |\n| `development`  | `dev`  |\n| `staging`      | `stg`  |\n| `prod`         | `prod` |\n| `production`   | `prod` |\n\nSelect *dev* and *development* \u2014 the query sees the SAME `dev` value in both cases and collapses to a single series. Before 12.4 you needed two variables or regex tricks to do this."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Chosen env (raw variable value)",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 13
      },
      "datasource": {
        "uid": "${ds_prom}",
        "type": "prometheus"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "count(up) * 0 + 1",
          "legendFormat": "env=${env:csv}"
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "textMode": "name"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "description": "Chosen env (raw variable value). Reference: https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/dashboards/variables/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "up{env=~\"${env:pipe}\"} \u2014 regex-joined via the pipe formatter",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 11,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 19
      },
      "datasource": {
        "uid": "${ds_prom}",
        "type": "prometheus"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "expr": "up{env=~\"${env:pipe}\"} or on() up",
          "legendFormat": "{{job}} {{instance}}"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 15
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom"
        }
      },
      "description": "up{env=~\"${env:pipe}\"} \u2014 regex-joined via the pipe formatter. Reference: https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/dashboards/variables/"
    }
  ]
}